-- New World Resources Drops From Three-Month High on Coal Prices
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-01-23T10:24:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/new-world-resources-drops-from-three-month-high-on-coal-prices.html
New World Resources Plc (NWR)  dropped from
an almost three-month high after the Czech coal company said it
cut delivery prices of the commodity in the first quarter.  NWR retreated 2.4 percent to 143.5 koruna as of 11:11 a.m.
in  Prague , after increasing 3.3 percent in the previous three
sessions to the highest level since Oct. 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  